==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːk|-iːk]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A mean, sneaking fellow.
# {{rfv-sense}} A ball bowled so as to roll along the ground; -- called also grub.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|sneaks|sneaking|''Commonwealth: '''[[sneaked]]''' ''or US and Commonwealth: '''[[snuck]]'''}}

# To [[creep]] or steal (away or about) privately; to come or go meanly, as a person afraid or ashamed to be seen; as, to sneak away from company.
# To [[hide]], especially in a mean or cowardly manner.

====Usage notes====
The past participle ''[[snuck]]'' has recently come into common usage, by analogy with [[strike]].  It is now acceptable in all but the most formal written Commonwealth English, but was rare prior to 1900.  This is the only irregular verb form to enter the language in several hundred years.  {{unreferenced}}

